{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641513","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641513"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:28:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:28:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17885"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17885"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10599"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114677"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10599","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10599"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17885"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96680"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5102"},{"type":"tags","id":"7603"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24702"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24704"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114677"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGlucagon is a pancreatic hormone that plays a crucial role in glucose homeostasis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the intracellular signalling pathway of glucagon?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Activates protein kinase A via cyclic AMP","Increases adenosine diphosphate concentration","Decreases adenylate cyclase activity","Inhibits cyclic AMP production","Stimulates protein phosphatase activity"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActivates protein kinase A via cyclic AMP\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. When glucagon binds to its G-protein coupled receptor on hepatocytes, it activates adenylate cyclase. This increases intracellular cyclic AMP (cAMP) levels, which then activates protein kinase A (PKA). PKA phosphorylates various enzymes to promote glucose production through glycogenolysis and gluconeogenesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases adenosine diphosphate concentration\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucagon signalling primarily involves cAMP, not ADP\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreases adenylate cyclase activity\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucagon activates rather than inhibits adenylate cyclase\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits cyclic AMP production\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucagon increases rather than decreases cAMP levels\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates protein phosphatase activity\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucagon works through protein kinases, not phosphatases\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis signalling cascade ultimately leads to increased blood glucose levels, which is the primary physiological role of glucagon.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Glucagon primarily acts on the liver to increase blood glucose levels by promoting glycogenolysis and gluconeogenesis.","Protein kinase A (PKA) is activated by increased cyclic AMP levels in response to glucagon binding.","The glucagon signalling cascade involves G-protein coupled receptor activation of adenylate cyclase."],"references":["Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 79, pg. 982.","Bender DA, Cunningham SM. Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. Boca Raton: CRC Press; 2021.","Salway JG. Metabolism at a glance. 4th ed. Chichester: John Wiley \u0026 Sons; 2016.","Chandel NS. Amino acid metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Apr 1;13(4):a040584.","Ling ZN, Jiang YF, Ru JN, Lu JH, Ding B, Wu J. Amino acid metabolism in health and disease. Signal Transduct Target Ther. 2023 Sep 13;8(1):345.","Nakrani MN, Wineland RH, Anjum F. Physiology, glucose metabolism. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan. Updated 2023 Jul 17.","Chandel NS. Carbohydrate metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Jan 4;13(1):a040568."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96680"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17885"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96680","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96680"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-18T15:03:37+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-18T15:03:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10599"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114677"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identif